# Goal Description
The user wants to know why new users start with a score of 22 and how to improve it. They also want the "Executive Career Advice" to be formatted nicely as bullet points instead of a single paragraph block.

## Explanation of Score (22/100)
The readiness score is calculated using [calculateReadinessScore](file:///d:/project/Skill_Gap%20Analyser%20and%20placement%20intelligence/server/services/skillGapAnalysis.service.js#257-281) in [server/services/skillGapAnalysis.service.js](file:///d:/project/Skill_Gap%20Analyser%20and%20placement%20intelligence/server/services/skillGapAnalysis.service.js). For a default 'Software Engineer', there are four core skills:
- Data Structures & Algorithms (Weight: 15)
- Object-Oriented Programming (Weight: 12)
- SQL (Weight: 10)
- Git (Weight: 8)
Total weight = 45. 
If a user registers or connects with only a matching skill of "SQL", their partial score is 10. [(10 / 45) * 100 = 22.2](file:///d:/project/Skill_Gap%20Analyser%20and%20placement%20intelligence/server/services/skillGapAnalysis.service.js#8-12), which rounds to **22**. 
**How to improve:** Students need to add more core skills matching exactly the requirements (e.g., "Data Structures & Algorithms", "Object-Oriented Programming", "Git") to their profile, or wait for the system admin to broaden the scoring criteria.

## Proposed Changes

### server
#### [MODIFY] [SkillGapAnalysis.js](file:///d:/project/Skill_Gap%20Analyser%20and%20placement%20intelligence/server/models/SkillGapAnalysis.js)
- Modify the `careerAdvice` field schema type from `String` to `[String]` (array of strings) to properly store an array of advice points. Mongoose will seamlessly wrap existing string values into an array with one element if previously stored.

#### [MODIFY] [skillGapAnalysis.service.js](file:///d:/project/Skill_Gap%20Analyser%20and%20placement%20intelligence/server/services/skillGapAnalysis.service.js)
- Change the Gemini prompt so the JSON output structure for `career_advice` expects an array of strings: `["Advice point 1", "Advice point 2", ...]`.
- Update the mock AI response and fallback mechanism to return an array of strings.
- Add robust parsing in [parseAIResponse](file:///d:/project/Skill_Gap%20Analyser%20and%20placement%20intelligence/server/services/skillGapAnalysis.service.js#220-256) to ensure `career_advice` is always an array of strings.

### client
#### [MODIFY] [SkillGapOverview.jsx](file:///d:/project/Skill_Gap%20Analyser%20and%20placement%20intelligence/client/src/components/student/SkillGapOverview.jsx)
- Update the rendering of the `careerAdvice` field. Since it will become an array of strings, we will map over these strings and display them as an unordered bullet list (`<ul>` and `<li>`) with proper spacing, margin, and typography enhancements. If it's a string, we can split it by newlines.

## Verification Plan
### Manual Verification
1. I will explain the score of 22 to the user.
2. The user will be requested to review this change and the explanation.
3. If they test the new analysis, they will see nicely formatted bullet points in the "Expert Guidance" section.
